2014-07-02  Christoph Mahrl <is121018@fhstp.ac.at>

	* src/dchat.c: 
		-) in main`()`: a cli_option_t structure will be crafted
		containing all available DChat command line options
		-) moved `usage()` and `fatal()` to log.c

	* src/dchat_h/option.h: 
		-) new header file; contains structure `cli_option_t` and
		important pre-processor defines and macros for ccommand line
		options.

	* src/option.c: 
		-) new source file; contains functions to extract a GNU
		short/long option string using the information stored in
		a `struct cli_option_t` structure. It contains other functions
		used to handle storing of options and retrieving information
		about them.

	* src/log.c: 
		-) changed signature of `usage()`. It requires an exit status
		a `cli_option_t` pointer, size of `cli_option_t` array, format string
		and variable arguments. 

2014-06-27  Christoph Mahrl <is121018@fhstp.ac.at>

	* src/dchat.c:
		-) major changes to support the redesign of the DChat
		   protocol and work with TOR.
		-) overall code refactoring and cleanup.

	* src/dchat_h/types.h: 
		-) renamed `dchat_types.h` to `types.h`

	* src/cmdinterpreter.c: 
		-) renamed `dchat_cmd.c` and `dchat_cmd.h` to
		   `cmdinterpreter.c` and `cmdinterpreter.h`.

	* src/network.c: 
		-) renamed `dchat_network.c` and `dchat_network.h` to
		   `network.c` and `network.h`.

	* src/contact.c: 
		-) renamed `dchat_contact.c` and `dchat_contact.h` to
		   `contact.c` and `contact.h`.

	* src/decoder.c: 
		-) renamed `dchat_decoder.c` and `dchat_decoder.h` to
		   `decoder.c` and `decoder.h`.

2014-06-22  Christoph Mahrl <is121018@fhstp.ac.at>

	* src/util.c:
		-) changed function signature and renamed function
		   `ansi_ter_clear_line()` and `ansi_term_cr()`.
		-) `print_dchat_msg`: added new parameter `nickname` 
		    to function signature.

	* src/dchat.c: 
		-) in `main()`: for remote connections `sockaddr_storage`
		   will be used. If a remote port has been specified
		   but no remote address, it will connect to the address
		   stored as listening ip in the global config to the 
		   specified port.

	* src/dchat_contact.c: 
		-) in `check_duplicates()`: compares own contact info
		   with the client stored in the contactlist. If it is
		   us, the index will be returned (for deletion).

	* src/dchat_decoder.c: 
		-) supporing nicknames in functions `decode_header()`
		   and `encode_header()`

	* src/dchat_h/dchat_decoder.h: 
		-) added preproc define header field `HDR_NICKNAME`.

	* src/dchat_h/dchat_types.h: 
	    -) in struct `dchat_pdu`: added new header field 
		   nickname.

2014-06-21  Christoph Mahrl <is121018@fhstp.ac.at>

	* src/dchat.c: 
		-) in `init()`: added sigmask to block certain signals
		-) `th_new_input()` is now the main thread function. Changed
		   return value to int. 0 will be returned on success and
		   -1 if an error occured.
		   Also the prompt is now colored yellow by calling the
		   function `ansi_color_bold_yellow()`.
		-) in `th_new_conn()`: added thread cancelation and cleanup 
		   handler
		-) in `th_main_loop()`: added thread cancelation and cleanup
		   handler; changed return value to void* - nothing will
		   be returned.
		-) in `main()`: no signals will be raised for termination
		   instead `destroy()` will be called directly and a return
		   happens afterwards.
		   Changed names of long options from `dst` to `dest`and
		   `nick` to `nickname`

	* src/util.c: 
		-) added ansi terminal escape code functions to print colors
		   and reset attributes.
		-) `print_dchat_msg()` calls `ansi_color_bold_cyan()` to
		   colorize the text message cyan.

	* src/dchat_h/dchat_types.h: 
		-) in struct `dchat_conf`: added pthread_t `select_th` and
		   removed pthread_t `userin_th`.

2014-06-20  Christoph Mahrl <is121018@fhstp.ac.at>

	* src/dchat.c: 
		-) in `main()`: supporting getopt_long()
		-) moved `getifaddr()` to parse network interfaces from
		   `init_global_config()` to `main()`
	* src/dchat.c: 
	    -) updated `usage(`)

